solutions.content:
# Intuition
The code is trying to solve the strong password checker problem1, which is to find the minimum number of steps required to make a given password strong.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Greedy algorithm  It first checks the length and the missing types of characters in the password, and then counts the number of repeating characters in a row.and the number of changes that can be done by deleting one or two characters. It then adjusts these variables according to the length of the password and returns the maximum of the missing types and the total changes.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n) where n is the length of the password.

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(1) as the code only uses constant extra space for variables.

# Code
```
#include <string>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

class Solution {
public:
    int strongPasswordChecker(string password) {
        int length = password.size();
        int missing_type = 3;
        if (any_of(password.begin(), password.end(), [](char c){ return islower(c); })) missing_type--;
        if (any_of(password.begin(), password.end(), [](char c){ return isupper(c); })) missing_type--;
        if (any_of(password.begin(), password.end(), [](char c){ return isdigit(c); })) missing_type--;

