```
/*let n = number of characters in the array "password"
(1) password should have at least 1 lowercase letter, 1 uppercase letter and 1 digit.
We declare these 3 boolean variables:
hasLowerCase: true if password has a lowercase letter
hasUpperCase: true if password has an uppercase letter
hasDigit: true if password has a digit

int basic = hasLowerCase(1/0) + hasUpperCase(1/0) + hasDigit(1/0)
if (basic==3), we met the first criterion.

The function helperLUD() will compute hasLowerCase, hasUpperCase, hasDigit and basic 
*/

/*
(2) If (n<6) we need to add (6-n) charaters to password.
The insertion and replacement of characters will break any sequence of 3 or more repeating characters.
e.g./ "aaaaa" -> "aaaBaa" -> "aa1Baa" (okay) => count = 2
e.g./ "aaaBB" -> ""aa1BB" => count = 1
e.g./ "aaaB1" -> "aaAaB1" => count = 1
In this manner, we don't have to carry out extra steps to break down any sequenc of same characters.
We first (2.1) add character(s) to password so that size=6, and at the same time,
    basic is added by (6-n) until it reaches 3, i.e. basic=min{3, basic+(6-n)};
then (2.2) replace characters with ones of missing types 

=> count = (6-n) + (3-min{3, basic+(6-n)})
*/

/*
(3) If (6<=n<=20) we will not insert any character to password (or delete any from it).
We would introduce the unordered map (uMap) to record sequences of same characters 
appearing 3 or more times in a row. 
e.g./ "aaaaaaaAAAAAA6666"
(i=6) the character 'a' is the last character of the sequence of 7 'a's => uMap[6]=7
(i=12) This 'A' is the last character of the sequence => uMap[12]=6
(i=16) This '6' is the last character of the sequence => uMap[16]=4
In general,
    uMap[index of the last character of a sequence] = length of the sequence of same characters (>=3)

The function helperThree() will serve as a seperate function to compute uMap

We will loop over uMap to count how many characters we have to replace in password.
    count = SUM_{i} (uMap[i]/3)
Just like what we did in (2), every time of replacement will help us increase basic up to 3.
If (basic<3), then we have to do (3-basic) times of replacement.
*/

/*
(4) If (n>20) we let extra=n-20 be the number of characters we have to delete from password
Since password may contain sequences of the same characters 3 or more times in a row,
we have to delete characters from password which generate the most benefits to us.

e.g./ password="aaabbbbcccccccdddee123dd", n=24 => extra=4
'a': uMap[2] = 3
'b': uMap[6] = 4
'c': uMap[13] = 7
'd': uMap[16] = 3

Deleting an 'a' from "aaa" will immediately break down the sequence "aaa(b)..."
=> password'= "aabbbbcccccccdddee123dd", count=1 and extra=3
'a': uMap[2] = 2 (removed from uMap)
'b': uMap[6] = 4
'c': uMap[13] = 7
'd': uMap[16] = 3

Delete a 'd' from "ddd" breaks down the sequence "ddd"
=> password' = "aabbbbcccccccddee123dd", count=2 and extra=2
'b': uMap[6]=4
'c': uMap[13]=7
(we don't touch other keys or values in uMap because we just FORMALLY erase character(s) from password,
but in practice, we don't have to)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The above deletion of characters should be carried out in an optimal manner.
It means that we break down as many sequences of 3 or more same characters as possible 
given that the number of extra characters (extra) is fixed.

In this example, we see that 
'a': uMap[2]%3 = 3%3 = 0
'b': uMap[6]%3 = 4%3 = 1
'c': uMap[13]%3 = 7%3 = 1
'd': uMap[16]%3 = 3%3 = 0
Therefore, an 'a' or 'd' should be deleted first before we deal with 'b' or 'c'

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Now, we delete two 'c's so that "ccc-ccc-c" becomes "ccc-cc".
Before this deletion, we need two times of replacement to break the sequence of 'c's,
for example, "ccccccc" -> "ccAcc0c"
After this deletion, we only need one time of replacement: "ccccc" -> "ccAcc"
=> password' = "aabbbbcccccddee123dd", count=4, extra=0

Right now, all replacement of characters which could break down a sequence of same characters have been done
=> we just replace characters in every sequence just like what we did in (3).

"aabbbbcccccddee123dd" -> "aabbAbccBccddee123dd"
count = 4 + 2 = 6

If (extra>0), then we delete extra number of characters directly from password.
If (basic<3), then we replace characters with ones of the missing types.
*/


class Solution {
public:
    bool hasLowerCase;
    bool hasUpperCase;
    bool hasDigit;
    int change;
    int basic;
    //
    int repeat;
    std::unordered_map<int, int> uMap; //uMap[last_index] = repeat
    std::unordered_map<int, int>::iterator itu;
    std::unordered_set<int> dSet;
    //
    int extra;

    void helperLUD(std::string& password, int& n){
        basic = 0;
        for (int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if (!hasLowerCase && password[i]>='a' && password[i]<='z'){
                hasLowerCase = true;
                basic++;
                continue;
            }

            if (!hasUpperCase && password[i]>='A' && password[i]<='Z'){
                hasUpperCase = true;
                basic++;
                continue;
            }

            if (!hasDigit && password[i]>='0' && password[i]<='9'){
                hasDigit = true;
                basic++;
            }
        }   
        return;
    }


    void helperThree(std::string& password, int& n){
        repeat = 1;
        for (int i=1; i<n; i++){
            if (password[i]==password[i-1]){
                repeat++;
            }else{
                if (repeat>=3){
                    uMap[i-1] = repeat;
                }
                repeat = 1;
            }
        }
        if (repeat>=3){
            uMap[n-1] = repeat;
        }
        repeat = 1;
        return;
    }

    int strongPasswordChecker(string password) {
        int n = password.size();
        hasLowerCase = false;
        hasUpperCase = false;
        hasDigit = false;
        change = 0;
        int temp = 0;
        bool stopLoop;
        //
        if (n<6){
            helperLUD(password, n);
            basic = std::min(3, basic+(6-n));
            change += 6-n;
            if (basic<3){
                change += (3-basic);
            }
            return change;
        }
        //
        if (n>=6 && n<=20){
            helperLUD(password, n);
            helperThree(password, n);
            for (itu=uMap.begin(); itu!=uMap.end(); itu++){
                temp = (itu->second/3);
                change += temp;
                if (basic<3){
                    basic = std::min(3, basic+temp);
                }
            }
            if (basic<3){
                change += (3-basic);
            }
            return change;
        }
        //
        if (n>20){
            extra = n-20;
            helperLUD(password, n);
            helperThree(password, n);

            while (extra>0 && uMap.size()>0){
                stopLoop = true;
                //delete extra elements: "baa(a)b"
                for (itu=uMap.begin(); itu!=uMap.end(); itu++){
                    if (extra>=1 && itu->second>=3 && itu->second%3==0){
                        change++;
                        itu->second--;
                        extra--;
                        if (itu->second<3){
                            dSet.insert(itu->first);
                        }
                        stopLoop = false;
                    }
                }

                //delete extra elements: "baa(aa)b"
                for (itu=uMap.begin(); itu!=uMap.end(); itu++){
                    if (extra>=2 && itu->second>3 && itu->second%3==1){
                        change+=2;
                        itu->second-=2;
                        extra-=2;
                        if (itu->second<3){
                            dSet.insert(itu->first);
                        }
                        stopLoop = false;
                    }
                }

                //delete extra elements: "baa(aaa)b"
                for (itu=uMap.begin(); itu!=uMap.end(); itu++){
                    if (extra>=3 && itu->second>3 && itu->second%3==2){
                        change+=3;
                        itu->second-=3;
                        extra-=3;
                        if (itu->second<3){
                            dSet.insert(itu->first);
                        }
                        stopLoop = false;
                    }
                }

                for (auto it=dSet.begin(); it!=dSet.end(); it++){
                    uMap.erase(*it);
                }
                dSet.clear();

                if (stopLoop) break;

                //std::cout<<"uMap.size() = "<<uMap.size()<<"\n";
                //std::cout<<"extra = "<<extra<<"\n";
            }//while (extra, uMap)

            //replace
            for (itu=uMap.begin(); itu!=uMap.end(); itu++){
                if (itu->second>=3){
                    change += (itu->second)/3;
                    if (basic<3){
                        basic = std::min(3, basic+(itu->second)/3);
                    }
                    itu->second = (itu->second)%3;
                }                
            }


            change += extra;

            if (basic<3){
                change += (3-basic);
            }
            return change;
        }

        return -1;

    }
};
```

