Here shares my solution without any further cleaning, which is exactly my thought process. The way the loops are written means this can usually be greatly simplified with some math.

Why so many downvote for the problem I guess this will be too stressful in an interview and the solution won't help any other problem. The intuition at the beginning I pretty much wrote down in 3 minutes; going ahead to implement it is a gamble, and code 90 lines (less lines would require more time) in 40min? No. I didn't clean the code so it is easier for you to understand the algorithm.

Keep points,
1. How to handle missing character type? Keep a count (max 3) and decrease it with any operation (add/replace) that can fix a type. This way missing types are fixed while doing other operations so is optimal.
2. Which chars to delete? First delete 1 char from all 3k len seqs, then 2 chars from all 3k+1 len seqs, then the rest. Just draw it out in a code comment and you will see.

Proof of the greedy correctness? Too tiring not sure I can do it now.

```
class Solution {
    public int strongPasswordChecker(String password) {
        // Greedy
        // 1. Find all consecutive chars.
        //    If total more than 20, delete till 2 or 20.
        //    If total is less than 6, insert after every 2, else replace the next one.
        // 2. Keep a count of above operations, that can cover missing types. If still missing, add till 6 then replace.
        // 3. If still less than 6. Add (however) till 6. If more than 20, remove (however) till 20.
        // Miss any case?

        int len = password.length();
        boolean seenLower = false;
        boolean seenUpper = false;
        boolean seenDigit = false;

        int ops = 0;

        List<Integer> tobreak = new ArrayList<>();

        Character prev = null;
        int cnt = 0;
        for (char c : password.toCharArray()) {
            if ('a' <= c && c <= 'z') seenLower = true;
            if ('A' <= c && c <= 'Z') seenUpper = true;
            if ('0' <= c && c <= '9') seenDigit = true;
            if (prev == null || c != prev) {
                if (cnt >= 3) {
                    if (len > 20 && cnt % 3 == 0) {
                        // delete 1 from aaaaaa
                        cnt--;
                        len--;
                        ops++;
                    }
                    if (cnt >= 3) tobreak.add(cnt);
                }
                prev = c;
                cnt = 1;
            } else {
                cnt++;
            }
        }
        if (cnt >= 3) {
            if (len > 20 && cnt % 3 == 0) {
                cnt--;
                len--;
                ops++;
            }
            if (cnt >= 3) tobreak.add(cnt);
        }

        int typeReq = 0;
        if (!seenLower) typeReq++;
        if (!seenUpper) typeReq++;
        if (!seenDigit) typeReq++;

        for (int i = 0; i < tobreak.size(); i++) { 
            int c = tobreak.get(i);
            if (len > 21 && c % 3 == 1) {
                // delete 2 from aaaa
                len -= 2;
                c -= 2;
                ops += 2;
                tobreak.set(i, c);
            }
        }

        for (int c : tobreak) {            
            if (len > 20) {
                // aaaaa or it no longer matters
                int r = Math.min(len - 20, c - 2);
                len -= r;
                c -= r;
                ops += r;
            }

            while (c > 2 && len < 6) { // usually this loop can be replaced with math
                // add 1 char after every 2
                len++;
                c -= 2;
                ops++;
                typeReq--;
            }

            // replace every 3rd char
            ops += c / 3;
            typeReq -= c / 3;
        }

        if (len < 6) {
            ops += 6 - len;
            typeReq -= 6 - len;
        }
        if (len > 20) ops += len - 20;

        if (typeReq > 0) ops += typeReq;

        return ops;
    }
}
